<TEXT>
a strong earthquake with an estimated magnitude of 6 
on the richter scale shook the tokyo area this morning the central 
meteorological agency said 
there were no immediate reports of injuries or property damage 
and no danger of a tsunami or tidal wave the agency said 
it said the temblor which hit at 1022 am was centered 31 
miles underground in the pacific ocean about 8 miles off the east 
coast of chiba state or about 29 miles east of tokyo 
new tokyo international airport at narita near the epicenter 
closed the runway for five minutes to check for damage 
buildings here shook quite violently but there was no damage 
no broken windows or anything so far said an airport official 
there was no delay of flights 
two rapidtransit bullet trains traveling northwest of tokyo 
halted for about six minutes and other trains stopped to check for 
track damage officials said 
the richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake at its 
epicenter according to ground motion as recorded on seismographs 
an earthquake of 6 on the scale is considered severe capable of 
widespread damage near the epicenter 
the quake came days after a strong temblor hit peru and another 
quake hit romania bulgaria and southern moldavia in the soviet 
union 
</TEXT>
