<TEXT>
an unmanned module containing facilities to produce 
highquality semicondutors in zero gravity was launched to 
rendezvous with the mir space station soviet media reported 
the kristall space module is to link up june 6 with the mir 
where cosmonauts anatoly solovyov and alexander balandin have been 
working for nearly four months according to soviet tv and the tass 
news agency 
the launch thursday from the baikonur space center in soviet 
central asia was delayed several times in recent days because of 
computer problems tass said the agency reported earlier in may 
that the modules launch was postponed due to problems relating to 
its eventual docking with the mir it did not elaborate 
once the spacecraft docks with the mir solovyov and balandin 
will conduct technological experiments using the orbital 
miniplant as flight technicians have dubbed the kristall module 
tass said 
the semiconductors produced in zero gravity can be used in solar 
batteries aboard the mir tass said the kristall module reportedly 
contains enough material to produce several solar battery elements 
scientists want to compare the quality of the material produced 
in orit with that manufactured on earth tass said 
