<TEXT>
a black college student who complained she was the 
victim of a campaign of racial harassment likely staged the 
incidents herself the prosecutor said thursday 
however emory university freshman sabrina collins wont be 
prosecuted for the allegedly false accusations which were widely 
reported at a time when racial tension seemed to be on the rise on 
us college campuses 
authorities hinted from early on they were suspicious the 
scrawled racist invective in ms collins dormitory room was a hoax 
even though the harassment was said to have caused her to collapse 
unable to speak on april 10 but neither university officials 
police nor prosecutors publicly stated those suspicions 
on thursday dekalb county solicitor ralph bowden released a 
letter to the georgia bureau of investigation saying he wouldnt 
press charges against ms collins the letter suggests but doesnt 
state that he has concluded she staged the harassment 
there certainly is some direct evidence and a great deal of 
circumstantial evidence that would cause one to believe that 
sabrina was the only person involved in these matters bowden told 
the new york times that is certainly the conclusion of the 
investigating agencies and i have no quarrel with that based on a 
reading of their reports 
bowdens office prosecutes misdemeanors a letter similar to his 
was released thursday by dekalb county district attorney bob wilson 
who handles misdemeanors 
there is substantial evidence which contradicts ms collins 
allegations wilsons letter says 
ms collins attorney james howard disputed those who blame the 
incidents on her 
it is apparent that the person who inflicted this pain and 
suffering upon her is not only free to do it again but has succeeded 
in evading the investigation howard said in a statement issued 
thursday 
state rep tyrone brooks of atlanta who has been an advisor to 
emory students in the wake of the collins incident urged 
authorities to keep the investigation open and prosecute even if 
ms collins is found to be the culprit 
what they want to do is blame the victim place a cloud over 
the victim publicly in the media and then walk away brooks said 
the investigation should not be left just hanging in the air 
whomever is responsible for these acts of vandalism needs to be 
apprehended and prosecuted no matter who it is 
the times quoting unidentified officials familiar with an 
unreleased report by the state bureau of investigation said it 
noted her accounts of harassment apparently coincided with a 
university investigation of suspicions she cheated in a chemistry 
class 
in declining to prosecute bowden said it appeared ms collins 
suffered from serious emotional problems he suggested counseling 
and treatment 
ms collins was hospitalized after she collapsed and became mute 
april 10 her family said she had lifted a rug in her room and found 
the words die nigger die scribbled in nail polish on the floor 
some students held silent protests and group meetings saying 
racism is a timehonored tradition at emory where 7 percent of the 
9500 students are black 
ms collins earlier had reported incidents in which pictures were 
broken bleach was poured on some of her clothes stuffed animals 
were mutilated and the phrase nigger hang was found written on 
the wall in her closet 
emory police first said they couldnt understand how the 
incidents continued after they installed an alarm in ms collins 
room they later theorized that someone had entered the room only 
once concealing some of the vandalism so it would be discovered 
later 
</TEXT>
