<TEXT>
archibald roosevelt jr a grandson of 
president theodore roosevelt and a retired cia officer died 
thursday of congestive heart failure at his home he was 72 
roosevelt served as cia station chief in istanbul madrid and 
london before retiring from the agency in 1974 he then became vice 
president of the chase manhattan bank based in washington 
he was active in diplomatic circles during the reagan 
administration when his wife selwa showker roosevelt was chief of 
protocol at the state department 
roosevelt was born to high social position in boston graduating 
from harvard college in 1940 in the same class as president kennedy 
he won a rhodes scholarship to oxford university but he was unable 
to take it because of world war ii 
an army intelligence officer in the war he joined the central 
intelligence group the immediate predecessor of the cia in 1947 
and served for 27 years always under diplomatic cover 
some have written that he had a hand in various coups of the 
early 1950s notably the overthrows of king farouk in egypt and 
nationalist iranian prime minister mohammed mossadegh 
but roosevelt was the soul of discretion in his 1988 memoirs 
for lust of knowing memoirs of an intelligence officer 
in it he did not even list his duty stations but he did tip 
off an interviewer to check his whos who entry to figure them out 
roosevelt confessed a fascination with the middle east and 
languages learning about 20 including uzbek 
the intelligence officer must not only know whose side he is 
on but have a deep conviction that he is on the right side he 
should not imitate the cynical protagonists of john lecarres 
novels essentially craftsmen who find their side no less amoral 
than the other roosevelt once wrote 
besides his wife he is survived by a son by a first marriage 
that ended in divorce and two grandchildren 
