technology 
engineering standards used to build i880 and the bay bridge in 
the 1930s and 1950s and other structures were adequate for 
engineering knowledge at that time but seismic standards were very 
low compared to those in use today the report said 
the oct 17 earthquake measured 71 on the richter scale caused 
an estimated 7 billion in damages and killed 67 people including 
42 in the freeway collapse 
crews took one month to repair a 50foot stretch of the upper 
deck of the bay bridge that crashed to the lower deck the cypress 
viaduct remains closed 
the panel said the doubledeck cypress structure collapsed 
because it was built on soft soil and its upright support columns 
and connecting joints werent strong enough to hold up the upper 
deck the shaking literally pulled the structure apart the report 
said 
gov george deukmejian who attended the oakland meeting where 
the 272page report was released said the report will help because 
it tells state officials what we should do and how to go about 
it 
deukmejian said he hoped voters tuesday would approve proposition 
111 which would increase the gasoline tax by 9 cents some of the 
extra funds should be used to retrofit the states highways and 
bridges in line with report recommendations he said 
the loma prieta earthquake should be considered a clear and 
powerful warning to the people of california housner said we 
have made progress during the last two decades in reducing 
earthquake risks but much more could have been done and awaits 
doing 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

