typical corporate response 
the company set up a committee 
blue cross usually throws a retirement lunch at a fancy hotel for 
employees of a decade or more complete with flowers photographs 
and a 100 gift certificate the guest of honor can invite up to 35 
coworkers and a handful of managers attend 
the nonprofit health insurance company with about 2 million 
subscribers in the philadelphia area picks up the 1200 tab up to 
20 times a year but mrs mclaughlin 64 wasnt interested in 
sitting through a bunch of speeches by executives she hardly knows 
you ride the elevator with these people and they dont have the 
