report thursday that 44 states and the district of columbia have 
laws restricting minors access to tobacco thirtysix states 
require cigarette buyers to be 18 three states set the age at 19 
four set it at 17 and one state and the district of columbia set it 
at 16 
kentucky louisiana missouri montana new mexico and wyoming 
