villages may have been buried by mudslides that resulted from the 
quake but civil defense officials could not confirm that about 40 
people were reported missing and hundreds were injured 
authorities in lima said the affected area was still without 
electricity water or telephone service 
at least three military transport planes carrying doctors 
medical and food supplies had arrived at the rioja airport by 
thursday afternoon according to the government neighboring chile 
offered to send tents for those left homeless 
thursday marked the 20th anniversary of a devastating earthquake 
that shook perus northern andes mountains killing 70000 people 
the 1970 quake registered 77 on the richter scale 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
