resuming relations we would not reject such a proposal he said 
he said britain would have to make it clear that it respects 
islam and moslems and condemns insults to islam such as those 
contained in rushdies book 
musavian said if britain revised its blasphemy law it would be 
a great step toward resumption of ties 
british moslems angered by rushdies book have demanded that the 
law which only applies to insults to christianity be changed to 
include islam 
hussein musawi leader of the shiite moslem fundamentalist islam 
amal in lebanon called last month for rushdies deportation from 
britain he said if britain expelled the author it would help gain 
release of british hostages in lebonon 
british officials said they would not deport rushdie 
musavian said he refused direct talks in dublin ireland with a 
british official last month because it was not clear what was on 
the agenda a british foreign office spokesman had said it was 
londons understanding that the iranians wanted a meeting 
asked whether iran would boost its current efforts to gain 
release of four britons missing in lebanon if diplomatic ties were 
restored musavian replied i cannot deny this 
the 16 western hostages in lebanon including six americans are 
believed held by proiranian moslem factions the longestheld is 
terry a anderson chief middle east correspondent of the associated 
press he was kidnapped march 16 1985 
musavian also said irans efforts will continue for release of 
all the hostages without any preconditions and for humanitarian 
reasons 
he said these efforts are unrelated to nationality bilateral 
relations negotiations or deals 
but he condemned the united states saying it had refused to make 
a goodwill gesture to iran and the kidnappers since the two american 
educators were released 
he said washington should help release hundreds of lebanese and 
palestinian moslems imprisoned in israel and in south lebanon 
if the united states and the west show good will and gain the 
release of most of the palestinian and lebanese moslems i have no 
doubt this will result in the release of all the hostages he said 
president bush has said he will make no deals to free the 
us hostages 
