<TEXT>
romania and bulgaria on friday began 
assessing the damage of an earthquake and more than 120 aftershocks 
that jolted central europe 
fourteen people were reported killed and 1000 injured as the 
quake rumbled through five countries wednesday nine people were 
killed in romania one in bulgaria and four in the soviet union the 
quake also struck turkey and yugoslavia but no deaths were reported 
in those countries 
the strongest aftershock rocked the greater part of romania and 
northern bulgaria at 318 am thursday thousands of people jumped 
from their beds and fled into the streets where many spent the rest 
of the night 
the aftershocks continued friday 
the romanian government trying to cope with its third major 
earthquake in 13 years said in a communique friday it would give 
top priority to repairs to buildings 
the ministry of national economy said it had no estimate of 
damage 
the northern bulgarian city of silistra on thursday appealed for 
aid saying it urgently needed glass cement bricks and tiles to 
repair damaged homes schools and a hospital the bulgarian news 
agency bta reported 
citing preliminary data bta said the quake destroyed 39 
residential buildings made 153 unfit to live in and damaged 6018 
more across the nation 
nineteen school buildings 11 kindergartens three hospitals and 
63 public and farm buildings also were damaged bta said 
dumitru enescu director of romanias earth physics institute 
said the quake and main aftershock were centered in the vrancea 
mountains part of the carpathian range about 200 miles northeast of 
bucharest 
we estimate that this seismological activity in vrancea and the 
aftershocks are going down and losing intensity he said 
richter scale readings of wednesdays quake from seismological 
stations around the world ranged from 65 to 75 putting it in the 
range of major to extremely powerful 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means that the ground 
motion is 10 times greater 
enescu said he believed the quake had a magnitude of between 65 
and 68 
the uppsala seismological center in sweden said the quake was 
very deep about 63 miles causing it to be felt so widely 
focsani capital of vrancea county where the quake was centered 
escaped without a shattered window but up to 20 romanians were 
slightly injured in thursdays powerful aftershock and two others 
were hurt more seriously medical assistant grigore nica said 
a prefabricated block of 64 apartments and the local bank 
suffered severe structural damage thursday city hall suffered major 
cracks in the ceiling and walls 
locksmith vasile ignat aid there was panic in focsani when the 
aftershock struck 
the power was cut off in certain areas people hit the street 
they panicked that another quake would come he said in the 
evening they no longer dared to go into their homes 
in bucharest a few camped out again in tents on thursday night 
but the panic subsided by friday 
some buildings in the capital suffered serious structural damage 
but otherwise the city escaped serious damage 
in northern bulgaria cities and villages on the danube river 
including ruse silistra and svishtov were panicstricken 
after thursdays strong aftershock bta reported it said thousands 
of people milled in the streets all night or fled in their cars 
</TEXT>
