soviet president mikhail s gorbachev in a 
move to break a summit stalemate has proposed the creation of a new 
council of all europe to play a decisive role in shaping the 
military future of germany us sources said friday 
the united states and the soviet union would participate in the 
deliberations along with other members of the nato and warsaw pact 
alliances as well as neutral countries 
gorbachev raised the idea with president bush at their opening 
summit session thursday the sources said and the two leaders 
assigned their top diplomatic aides to pursue the concept next week 
in copenhagen denmark and again in berlin later this month 
we are prepared to work with it it is not something we would 
reject out of hand said a us official familiar with the 
details he spoke only on condition he not be identified 
at the start of his second day of summit talks with bush 
