infestation 
thats because cars keep getting doused with a sticky mixture of 
malathion pesticide and corn syrup bait that is sprayed from 
helicopters in an effort to eradicate the pest spraying already has 
driven business up at car washes by an estimated 20 percent to 40 
percent as drivers wash their cars after each spraying car wash 
operators report 
and car washes have received a boost from metropolitan water 
district officials who through their literature are encouraging car 
owners to go to a car wash rather than wash cars on their own 
thats because mechanical car washes use just a fraction of the 
water used by the average motorist with a hose and bucket in the 
driveway as little as 15 gallons per car as opposed to 50 gallons 
