president rafael angel calderon 
announced an austerity plan that will slash government expenses and 
raise rates for public services to help bring down the deficit 
in a nationwide radio and television broadcast late wednesday 
calderon said the government deficit has rise to more than 320 
million this year more than 6 percent of the gross domestic product 
of this central american country of 29 million residents 
this massive deficit forces us to take necessary although 
hard measures to avoid the painful tax of inflation he said 
the government austerity policy will reduce spending by 70 
million this year he said forcing an increase in the price of 
fuel electricity water and telephone services 
to help reduce the impact of some of the price hikes a food 
assistance plan and other aid programs will be increased he said 
since taking office may 8 calderon has made reducing the deficit 
a main priority in 1989 under president oscar arias the deficit 
was about 220 million or 4 percent of the gross domestic product 
