<TEXT>
south koreans are applauding the first 
meeting between a south korean and a soviet leader as a milestone 
that will spur dramatic new dialogue with communist north korea 
presidents roh taewoo and mikhail s gorbachev are to meet in 
san francisco next monday after gorbachev ends summit talks with 
president bush 
seoul and moscow have no diplomatic relations the meeting was in 
the works for at least two months and has the blessing of the us 
government news reports said 
roh said the talks will be aimed at helping end hostility on the 
korean peninsula bitterly divided since 1945 into communist north 
and capitalist south koreans hope eased tensions will lead to 
unification 
the border between the two koreas is sealed and more than 1 
million troops are deployed behind barbed wire on either side 
washington and moscow have exerted pressure on their respective 
allies in seoul and north koreas capital of pyongyang to pursue 
dialogue little progress has been made 
since there is no way opened for me to go to pyongyang i have 
to go there by way of moscow said roh 
in seoul the stock market shot up on news of the rohgorbachev 
meeting a soviet trade show was flooded with koreans as intent on 
buying vodka as inspecting technology political leaders and 
editorials hailed the meeting as an extraordinary moment in korean 
history 
north korea released a statement monitored in tokyo suggesting 
it may end its boycott of dialogue with south korea it said the 
only way of solving the question of national unification in a 
peaceful way is to develop dialogue 
rohs popularity which plunged in recent months due to labor 
unrest and economic worries overnight appeared to rise 
i believe the meeting will bring an epochal change in 
relations between south and north korea said kim daejung head 
of the leading opposition party for peace and democracy i welcome 
it as a sign of great progress 
kim youngsam the leader of the governing democratic justice 
party who met gorbachev in moscow last march predicted a major 
breakthrough will be made in relations between the two countries 
kim also said the soviet union was expected to exercise 
influence upon the north to adopt an opendoor or reformist policy 
the projected summit will mark a historic milestone in the 
