however its not yet clear exactly what combination of weapons 
would be retired in order to remain within starts overall limit on 
ballistic missile warheads of 4900 
the soviets would be expected to retire several types of 
intercontinental ballistic missiles including 154 of their ss18s 
which are the centerpiece of their strategic nuclear force these 
missiles were deployed between 1975 and 1980 
the treaty is expected to allow at least some modernization of 
the remaining ss18s this provision however would be the only one 
in the treaty to put limits on individual weapons as a result both 
sides will be allowed virtually unlimited freedom to develop and 
deploy newer more accurate weapons later this decade 
