embassy in washington were clearly disappointed with bushs decision 
i think hes letting democracy and independence down said 
arunas martinonis of boston it really upsets me 
bush should be stronger about lithuania latvia and estonia 
said helen zimavicus carter who drove 15 hours from her chicago 
home to join the protest were really shocked he doesnt stand up 
for their rights 
in addition to the trade pact the two leaders reached agreement 
on a fiveyear grain purchase agreement us officials had said 
that the soviets were threatening to hold up signing this pact 
unless they got a trade agreement 
intense debate was taking place on the grain and trade proposals 
throughout much of the day as the soviets threatened to block the 
grain agreement advantageous to us farmers if they didnt get 
the trade pact they sought administration officials said 
however larger issues in ussoviet relations appeared to play 
more of a role in bushs decision to give gorbachev the trade pact 
