one point said the vagueness was intentional on whether the trade 
agreement would be signed 
the trade agreement sorely wanted by gorbachev was always 
bushs trump card officials suggested 
it was quite obvious that gorbachev was seeking something on 
the economic front said one official its obviously something 
that he wanted to take home 
to emphasize the importance he placed on a trade pact gorbachev 
took his lobbying campaign directly to members of congress earlier 
friday he told them that approval of a trade deal would be 
especially politically useful for him back home 
american and soviet negotiators reached agreement several weeks 
ago on the details for both a trade pact and a grain agreement in 
anticipation that both would be signed at the washington summit 
however the outcome of both deals was in doubt up until the signing 
ceremony friday 
the pact would be a step toward granting the soviet union 
mostfavorednation trade status qualifying it for the lowest 
tariffs granted to any country 
currently soviet products sold in the united states bear duties 
that are as much as 10 times higher than imports from other 
countries by one estimate the price of soviet vodka could drop by 
125 per bottle 
leading american business groups including the us chamber of 
commerce and the national association of manufacturers have also 
been lobbying for approval of the agreement warning that without 
the deal american companies will be at a disadvantage in trying to 
gain access to the vast soviet market 
the agreement would provide better copyright protection for 
american companies and cut down on the time us companies must wait 
for approval to begin commercial operations in the soviet union 
it would also clear the way for approval of governmentsubsidized 
loans and for loan guarantees from the exportimport bank and the 
overseas private investment corp 
analysts said this provision was significant because it would 
expand the number of us companies interested in setting up joint 
ventures in the soviet union a key goal of gorbachevs economic 
reforms 
gorbachev said his quest for the trade agreement did not 
represent a plea for special favors 
the grain accord would increase the minimum amount of us wheat 
feed grains soybeans and other commodities that the soviets would 
purchase from the current 9 million tons annually to 10 million tons 
the soviet union is the largest foreign market for american grain 
products and new grain pact was viewed as a top objective for us 
farm groups 
