<TEXT>
westinghouse electric corps board has voted 
to exempt the company from coverage under pennsylvanias tough new 
antitakeover law 
the company also said thursday it will start buying back up to 20 
million shares of its common stock 
the law signed april 27 is designed to protect 
pennsylvaniabased corporations from hostile raiders it has been 
sharply attacked by the investment community for sheltering 
management while denying stockholders the benefits of potential 
price speculation in their shares 
westinghouse is strongly committed to increasing shareholder 
value chairman john c marous said in a statement adding that 
customers employees suppliers and communities will benefit if the 
company continues to operate successfully 
companies have the right to exempt themselves from the law in the 
first 90 days of its existence 
the company said in a separate statement it will purchase the 
stock in public markets or through private sales during the next 
year and a half the company said it will use cash internally 
generated funds and shortterm debt 
the stock purchase is in keeping with our strategic direction 
of enhancing shareholder value marous said 
marous said the stock purchase is an attractive investment 
the stock closed thursday at 3637 up 137 on the new york 
stock exchange 
